01:25:45.180 --> 01:25:48.780
also activity-regulated paracrine factors that could play an

1464
01:25:48.820 --> 01:25:52.640
important mechanistic role. And so next we asked whether there

1465
01:25:52.660 --> 01:25:56.290
were secreted factors that could transmit part of this proliferative

1466
01:25:56.300 --> 01:25:59.840
effect in glioma. And to test that, we used a

1467
01:25:59.860 --> 01:26:02.790
conditioned media paradigm, which is we would

1468
01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:05.780
stimulate healthy cortical

1469
01:26:06.660 --> 01:26:10.580
brain slices with both wild type and channelrhodopsin positive with

1470
01:26:10.640 --> 01:26:11.520
patterned blue light.

1471
01:26:12.480 --> 01:26:12.810
And

1472
01:26:13.760 --> 01:26:17.720
channelrhodopsin-stimulated slices are associated with greater neuronal

1473
01:26:17.730 --> 01:26:20.020
activation and paracrine factor secretion

1474
01:26:20.860 --> 01:26:24.720
compared to the controls, and this also showed evidence that activity-regulated

1475
01:26:24.840 --> 01:26:28.640
factors are sufficient to promote G34 mutant glioma growth.

1476
01:26:29.240 --> 01:26:33.200
So at this point, the model becomes a bit more complete with G34

1477
01:26:33.260 --> 01:26:37.160
leveraging both circuitry integration and activity-dependent paracrine

1478
01:26:37.240 --> 01:26:41.060
signaling. So at this stage, we wanted to know

1479
01:26:41.120 --> 01:26:44.829
what secreted activity-regulated mitogens could be causing

1480
01:26:44.860 --> 01:26:48.040
this effect. And based on prior work in the lab,

1481
01:26:48.400 --> 01:26:52.020
brain-derived neurotrophic factor or BDNF and neuroligin

1482
01:26:52.220 --> 01:26:55.540
3 were both natural candidates, as both have been shown to

1483
01:26:56.040 --> 01:26:59.720
promote growth in other pediatric gliomas, specifically diffuse midline

1484
01:26:59.760 --> 01:27:01.280
glioma, as I mentioned earlier.

1485
01:27:02.480 --> 01:27:06.400
However, from our experiments and previously published data in the lab, we do

1486
01:27:06.440 --> 01:27:10.400
not see the same effect of these proteins in G34, which

1487
01:27:10.440 --> 01:27:13.840
told us something important, that even though this tumor type

1488
01:27:14.620 --> 01:27:18.280
seems to respond to neuronal activity, it does not appear to rely on the

1489
01:27:18.340 --> 01:27:22.140
same canonical paracrine factors that had been identified previously.

1490
01:27:22.620 --> 01:27:26.040
And this fits into the larger biology of the project as a

1491
01:27:26.180 --> 01:27:29.700
G34 mutant glioma is shown to be such a

1492
01:27:29.720 --> 01:27:33.620
distinct tumor type with a different developmental context and different

1493
01:27:33.640 --> 01:27:37.560
cell of origin. So if neural activity still promoted this growth,

1494
01:27:38.100 --> 01:27:41.700
there is probably some other activity factor that could be involved.

1495
01:27:41.840 --> 01:27:45.650
So this led us to run a proteomic analysis on the conditioned

1496
01:27:45.680 --> 01:27:47.680
media, which highlighted

1497
01:27:49.220 --> 01:27:53.040
neuronal cell adhesion factor or N-CADHERIN and neurofascin

1498
01:27:53.300 --> 01:27:56.900
as two highly upregulated candidate proteins of interest.

1499
01:27:58.600 --> 01:28:01.300
So next, we tested these candidates

1500
01:28:02.880 --> 01:28:06.060
in proliferation experiments and found that

1501
01:28:06.320 --> 01:28:10.260
N-CADHERIN increased proliferation in G34 mutant cells.

1502
01:28:10.640 --> 01:28:14.360
And importantly, this was also replicated in additional G34

1503
01:28:14.540 --> 01:28:18.420
mutant cell lines, and which shows that these molecules emerge

1504
01:28:18.500 --> 01:28:20.970
as a strong candidate as

1505
01:28:22.020 --> 01:28:24.660
a possible paracrine factor in this tumor subtype.

1506
01:28:27.000 --> 01:28:30.800
And we also wanted to know whether these factors might have

1507
01:28:30.840 --> 01:28:33.440
another effect in terms of migration.

1508
01:28:33.500 --> 01:28:37.220
So using a spheroid migration assay, we found that neurofascin

1509
01:28:37.320 --> 01:28:41.080
increased glioma migration distance over time across various time

1510
01:28:41.140 --> 01:28:45.120
points. So altogether, this supports that these proteins

1511
01:28:45.760 --> 01:28:49.300
can not only contribute to growth-related effects but also

1512
01:28:49.320 --> 01:28:51.420
invasion-related behavior.

1513
01:28:53.300 --> 01:28:56.780
And we also began to ask how these proteins might be exerting these effects,

1514
01:28:56.840 --> 01:29:00.700
so looking at transcriptional changes induced by N-CADHERIN

1515
01:29:00.740 --> 01:29:04.370
treatment. First, this volcano plot here shows that N-CADHERIN

1516
01:29:04.380 --> 01:29:07.860
exposure induced a broad change in gene expression with

1517
01:29:09.440 --> 01:29:13.120
many genes being upregulated and others being downregulated at the transcriptional

1518
01:29:13.180 --> 01:29:13.460
level.

1519
01:29:14.420 --> 01:29:17.360
And we also looked through a KEGG analysis.

1520
01:29:18.280 --> 01:29:21.920
We saw that there are various upregulated and downregulated changes across

1521
01:29:21.980 --> 01:29:25.480
multiple biological programs, specifically

1522
01:29:25.900 --> 01:29:29.770
ECM receptor interactions, adhesion, and signaling programs.

1523
01:29:30.580 --> 01:29:31.450
And finally,

1524
01:29:32.900 --> 01:29:36.540
this focuses on some functional categories that were upregulated

1525
01:29:36.640 --> 01:29:40.200
and cell differentiation and neurodifferentiation were some of the most

1526
01:29:40.440 --> 01:29:44.280
upregulated biological processes as a result of N-CADHERIN.

1527
01:29:44.440 --> 01:29:46.040
So in summary,

1528
01:29:47.440 --> 01:29:51.070
some major takeaways is that DHG/HDG34

1529
01:29:51.400 --> 01:29:54.820
mutant glioma appears to leverage both conserved and

1530
01:29:54.980 --> 01:29:57.560
subtype-specific mechanisms to integrate into

1531
01:29:57.580 --> 01:30:01.024
neurocircuitryWe see evidence of synaptic

1532
01:30:01.564 --> 01:30:04.304
structures, electrophysiological responsiveness,

1533
01:30:04.864 --> 01:30:07.684
activity-dependent growth, and paracrine influences.

1534
01:30:08.264 --> 01:30:11.944
And among these factors, NRCam and neurofascin emerge

1535
01:30:12.004 --> 01:30:15.984
as strong candidates with effects in both proliferation and

1536
01:30:16.004 --> 01:30:18.564
migration for future translational research.

