01:37:11.808 --> 01:37:14.568
solid tumors, and the difference is highly significant.

1656
01:37:15.248 --> 01:37:19.028
In terms of T-ALL, there can be tandem duplications spanning MIB

1657
01:37:19.088 --> 01:37:22.868
at 6q in about 8 to 15% of cases.

1658
01:37:23.308 --> 01:37:26.868
There are rarer T-cell receptor beta MIB rearrangements

1659
01:37:28.188 --> 01:37:32.058
are observed that juxtapose a T-cell receptor enhancer next to

1660
01:37:32.108 --> 01:37:35.608
the MIB gene. There can be somatic mutations that

1661
01:37:35.668 --> 01:37:38.848
introduce MIB binding motifs, creating a super enhancer

1662
01:37:38.888 --> 01:37:42.488
upstream of the TAL oncogene, and about

1663
01:37:42.528 --> 01:37:46.048
30% of MIB wild-type patients have MIB

1664
01:37:46.208 --> 01:37:47.028
overexpression.

1665
01:37:48.818 --> 01:37:49.008
Now,

1666
01:37:50.008 --> 01:37:51.128
many of you will know that

1667
01:37:52.068 --> 01:37:55.968
pre-mRNA is processed into RNA and translated into protein, but

1668
01:37:56.028 --> 01:37:59.808
about a third of genes can contain a poison exon or a premature

1669
01:37:59.868 --> 01:38:03.508
termination codon that when incorporated into the mature

1670
01:38:03.608 --> 01:38:07.598
mRNA, results in nonsense-mediated decay and degradation of

1671
01:38:07.688 --> 01:38:09.808
the mRNA and loss of the protein.

1672
01:38:10.788 --> 01:38:14.288
Now, REM422 promotes poison exon inclusion in the MIB

1673
01:38:14.888 --> 01:38:18.858
pre-mRNA, resulting in degradation of MIB RNA and

1674
01:38:18.888 --> 01:38:19.508
the protein.

1675
01:38:20.308 --> 01:38:23.328
It is a small molecule administered orally once daily.

1676
01:38:24.228 --> 01:38:27.448
It's been developed by Remix Therapeutics for the treatment of

1677
01:38:27.968 --> 01:38:31.588
AML and high-risk MDS and adenoid cystic

1678
01:38:31.688 --> 01:38:35.608
carcinoma, and is in clinical trials, and I believe it may have received FDA

1679
01:38:35.668 --> 01:38:37.748
approval for this malignancy just recently.

1680
01:38:38.508 --> 01:38:42.128
So it was of interest to us to test REM422

1681
01:38:42.208 --> 01:38:43.588
against the pivot

1682
01:38:44.428 --> 01:38:46.328
pediatric ALL PDX models.

1683
01:38:47.268 --> 01:38:50.908
Just an outline of the study. The aim was to assess the

1684
01:38:50.968 --> 01:38:54.728
single-agent efficacy of REM422 against a panel of 30 ALL

1685
01:38:54.828 --> 01:38:58.748
PDXs in a single mouse trial using immune-deficient NSG mice.

1686
01:38:59.138 --> 01:39:03.108
So we have one vehicle control and one REM422-treated mouse

1687
01:39:03.148 --> 01:39:03.948
per PDX.

1688
01:39:04.828 --> 01:39:08.578
These are orthotopic models. Human leukemia infiltrates the bone marrow,

1689
01:39:08.648 --> 01:39:11.428
spleen, other organs, and disseminates to the peripheral blood.

1690
01:39:11.468 --> 01:39:14.188
They're very aggressive, so it's a very high bar to get

1691
01:39:14.228 --> 01:39:17.728
efficacy with single agents.

1692
01:39:18.388 --> 01:39:22.108
We selected 30 PDXs with different levels of MIB mRNA expression,

1693
01:39:22.308 --> 01:39:26.268
and they're shown here on the right, representing the six major subtypes of B-ALL,

1694
01:39:26.868 --> 01:39:30.548
Ph-positive, Ph-like, KMT2A rearranged-ALL,

1695
01:39:30.908 --> 01:39:34.868
T-ALL, and early T-cell precursor ALL with various levels

1696
01:39:34.988 --> 01:39:37.128
of MIB mRNA expression.

1697
01:39:37.928 --> 01:39:41.488
REM422 was administered at five milligrams per kilogram daily for

1698
01:39:41.628 --> 01:39:45.308
21 days via oral gavage. It was very well tolerated.

1699
01:39:45.348 --> 01:39:48.548
Treatments began when individual mice reached 1% human

1700
01:39:48.748 --> 01:39:52.088
CD45 cells in the peripheral blood. So this is established disease.

1701
01:39:52.668 --> 01:39:56.248
This is about 50 to 60% infiltration of the bone marrow.

1702
01:39:56.288 --> 01:39:57.608
It's not developing disease.

1703
01:39:58.638 --> 01:40:01.408
The event criteria were when mice reached

1704
01:40:01.548 --> 01:40:05.508
25% leukemia cells in the peripheral blood or other ethically

1705
01:40:05.548 --> 01:40:09.368
approved endpoints. And the analysis was looking

1706
